narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Taking the basics learned in Czech 110, Czech 120 builds and expands upon these principles. I would recommend this course to those serious about furthering their ability in the Czech language.
Do not take this course, it used to be easy. Now it sucks.

I would recommend Czech to another student, as long as that student is interested in linguistics. Czech, though used relatively little in the world, is a fascinating language and embodies Yale - it is a chance to study something unique that few people get the chance to study. So yes, I would recommend Czech to another student, because Yale is about expanding your horizons and there are few better ways to do that than to study an exotic language with a native speaker of that language (Professor von Kunes).
